  <info>
    <title>Installation of virtualization components</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tbazant@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <xi:include href="../snippets/virt-components-intro.xml"/>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    You can install the virtualization tools required to run a &vmhost; either when installing the
    system (see the <link
    xlink:href="https://documentation.suse.com/sles/16.0/html/SLES-x86-64-agama-based-installation/index.html#agama-manual-installation">manual
    installation</link>), or from an alerady installed system by installing a virtualization pattern. The later
    option is described bellow:
  </para>
  
<screen>&prompt.sudo;zypper install -t pattern <replaceable>PATTERN_NAME</replaceable></screen>
<para>
  Replace the <replaceable>PATTERN_NAME</replaceable> with one of the following values:
</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><literal>kvm_server</literal></term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Installs a basic &vmhost; with the &kvm; and &qemu; environments.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><literal>kvm_tools</literal></term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Installs &libvirt; tools for managing and monitoring &vmguest;s in
          the &kvm; environment.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>    
  </variablelist>
</topic>
